{{Quote|Okay, Cherit's outfit supplied rak, lxetallic, and Twi'lek girls to some minor Kuati nobs. He was doing his deals here for a while. Maybe he was muscling in on your relative's turf.|[[Unidentified bartender (Paradise Cantina)|A bartender]] to the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]|<ref name="Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice">''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]''</ref>}}
'''Rak''' was a substance that the gang boss [[Cherit]] supplied to [[Kuati/Legends|Kuati]] nobles before his [[Death/Legends|death]] sometime around the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]]. Afterward, a [[Gender/Legends|man]] named [[L. Fraig]] continued [[Cherit's gang|Cherit's operation]].

==Behind the scenes==
Rak was briefly mentioned in [[2007]]'s ''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]'', a novel by [[Karen Traviss]].

